<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A school is preparing a rectangular garden for planting kales. The garden measures <m>{16.5}</m> m in length and <m>{7.7}</m> m in width. Find the area of the garden.
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <alert>2 decimal places</alert>.
</p>

<p>
Area = <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> <m>\text {m}^2</m>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The garden is rectangular.
</p>

<p>
The formula for the area of a rectangle is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = l \times w
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the dimensions.
</p>

<p>
<me>
l = {16.5}\text{ m}, \quad w = {7.7}\text{ m}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Substitute into the formula.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {16.5} \times {7.7}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Multiply.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {127.05}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Round to 2 decimal places.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A \approx {127.05}\text{ m}^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the garden is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{{127.05}\text{ m}^2}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>127.05</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>